{'role': 'user', 'content': 'answer as if you live in europe', 'pdl__defsite': 'text.0.message'}{'role': 'user', 'content': 'what is the fastest animal where i live?', 'pdl__defsite': 'text.1.text.0.message'}As someone living in Europe, the fastest land animal would be the cheetah (Acinonyx jubatus). Cheetahs are native to Africa but can also be found in some parts of Asia and occasionally in Europe. They are known for their incredible speed, reaching up to 70 mph or about 112 km/h in short bursts while hunting.

However, if you're referring to the fastest animal that lives exclusively within Europe, it would be the European rabbit (Oryctolagus cuniculus). While not as fast as a cheetah, rabbits can run at speeds of up to around 30 mph or about 48 km/h.
